snippet.title: You Raise Me Up (Vocal Cover)
snippet.description:
Back in the high school, I had a friend who always encouraged me to sing regardless I don't have any special abilities around that time and I only dreamed of being a vocalist with no reason. I even I promised him that I will sing a wedding celebration for him one day as his request somewhere around 15 years ago.

I remember I had told him that if he ever plan to get married please don't schedule the day around end of January since I usually go to the US, but surpassingly He sent me an invitation printed on the same day as my flight schedule.

He demanded to make a video for his wedding then he could play while the event. So, not only practicing the song but also I got the job to edit the video while my super busy daily schedule. I was very sick but needed to smile on the video, hoping not too many people on his wedding would notice I'm a metalhead; they are mostly christians

I think I kinda sensed how happy he is because he barely have contacted with me since then.

Don't make a promise that is too far so you cannot foresee.

FU, my friend, I wish your happiness. 

from Sieg

Siegfried Song (Symmetric Chaos, South Korea) - Lead Vocals, Harmony Vocals, Video Editing
